> [frayoshi](#comment_1_1By85xCDz7VyZEq9WjmhtbNaPKimQwhPLp): cool!!Just, the block all function seems like not working for me... could I be doing someting wrong?

It should work fine? What error is it giving? To add it manually you can just add the following to your /data/filters.json file under "includes"

```
"1CufK1ZtvekbFXEpSyKT2gDjf9jnqW8KwG/filters/users.json": {
      "address": "1CufK1ZtvekbFXEpSyKT2gDjf9jnqW8KwG", 
      "date_added": 1549539186.161785, 
      "description": null, 
      "inner_path": "filters/users.json"
    }
```

So it should look something like this:

```
{
  "includes": {
     "1CufK1ZtvekbFXEpSyKT2gDjf9jnqW8KwG/filters/users.json": {
      "address": "1CufK1ZtvekbFXEpSyKT2gDjf9jnqW8KwG", 
      "date_added": 1549539186.161785, 
      "description": null, 
      "inner_path": "filters/users.json"
    }
  }, 
  "mutes": {
   //all your muted users and such
 }
}
```
